        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Although critiques of Duke may not weigh as heavy on the heart as headlines of war, political corruption and human plight due to climate change, consuming negative news about the space we inhabit is likely to contribute to a negative perception, or negative “availability heuristic” of our surroundings.</p>
<p>The Chronicle could be a source of celebration of the joy, love and greatness that exist at Duke just as much as it is a platform to expose its problems. It’s time I do a better job of striking a balance.</p>
<p><em>Bella Miller is a Trinity senior. Her column, “make Duke weird,” runs on alternate Tuesdays.</em></p>

